# Linux Fundamentals 1

## Writeup Overview
This will cover background information about Linux

## Objectives
- Understand the reason Linux is used over other Operating systems
- Identify the core operations that make Linux valuable 

## Key Concepts
| Linux | Operating system family. Built around the 'Linux Kernel'|
|Distribution(distro) | A single full Linux OS. Built around a Linux kernel, such as Ubuntu, Fedora, Debian, Linux Mint, Arch |
| Unix | Older OS family. Strongly influenced Linux |
| Extensible | Capable of being expanded or added onto without 'rebuilding'. To support new functions, allow plugins/extensions or adapt to different uses |
| Terminal | text-based interface. Used to interact with an OS through commands |
| $ | Shell Prompt, for a regular user. Means a shell is ready |
| echo | Command that 'prints' text(to the terminal). Used to display text, show variable values, test commands, write text(into files) |
| whoami | Shows the username of the account a user is currently using |

### Linux Overview
- Strong control and customizaiton
- 'Powerful' commandline
- Popular in IT, networking, servers
- Offer may distros for free
- Considered more 'lightweight' than other OS
- Linux is used in websites, car entertainment/control panels, PoS terminals
- Linux is umbrella term(for multiple OS that are based on UNIX)
- Open-source OS
- Variants of Linux can be suited for specific systems(such as Ubuntu and Debian)
- Often is used without a GUI
- Most usage is through a terminal environment

### Linux Variants
- Ubuntu and Debian are considerd commonplace distributions
- Ubuntu can be ran as a web/application server or as a Desktop
- Ubuntu Server can run on systems with only (512MB of RAM)


## Security Relevance
- A large amount of modern systems run on Linux(web servers, cloud environments, containers, network appliances, security tools and IoT systems)
- Many security tools run on Linux(nmap, tcpdump,wireshark, grep, awk, ssh, iptables, nftables, fail2ban, Snort, Suricata)
- Used as a working environment for analysts, engineers, pentesters and admins

